column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/d5f528f14647b6270096921b917ee5379bdd19e5 for binaries and test log.\n
Please don't duplicate all the code with extract_strings_qt.py, move the common code to a function in a module and import it from both\n

Or better yet, if you just need to run it with Python installed in a non-standard location (not even Windows has a D:\ harddrive by default!), specify the script as a command line option to the Python EXE:

```
/d/Python27/python share/qt/extract_strings_qt.py
```
As, AFAIK ^^, I have no clue, how to `move the common code to a function in a module and import it from both` I'll just close this and use my local version ;).\n
